# Reuse UI components

## Required

Before adding a new input, picker, modal field, or action bar, **search `src/app/components/shared/` and existing modals** for an existing primitive. Extend it with props instead of styling a one-off.

### Form fields (app + onboarding)

| Use case | Component |
|----------|-----------|
| Text | `FormInput` from `FormFields.tsx` |
| Money | `CurrencyAmountInput` (wraps `FormInput` + currency glyph) |
| Month/year (looks like other inputs, opens month grid) | `MonthYearFieldInput` |
| Month filter pill (Expenses header, prev/next) | `MonthYearPill` — **not** for modal forms |
| App field colors (border, surface) | `appFormFieldStyle(c)` on all three above |

All app modal fields share **`formFieldStyle` height (50px)**. Do **not** use `formFieldStyleCompact` in bottom sheets unless the whole form is explicitly a compact density (and name/amount/date must match).

### Modals

- `BottomSheetModal` + `bottomSheetChrome` + `AppBottomSheetLayout` + `ModalActionBar`
- Month picker inside a modal: pass `zIndex` ≥ `MODAL_OVERLAY_Z + 50` to `MonthYearPickerDropdown` (default on `MonthYearFieldInput`)

### Do not

- Raw `<input>` with copy-pasted padding, radius, or colors when `FormInput` / `CurrencyAmountInput` fits
- New date/month controls that look different from `FormInput` in the same form
- Hard-code picker `z-index: 500` when the anchor is inside `#app-modal-host` (modal host is `z-index: 1000`)
- Duplicate `fieldStyle` objects — use `appFormFieldStyle(c)`

## Checklist before shipping form UI

- [ ] Text, money, and date fields use shared components above
- [ ] Same `tone` + `appFormFieldStyle(c)` (or onboarding dark styles) on every field in the form
- [ ] Dropdowns/portals above modals (`MODAL_OVERLAY_Z + 50` or higher)
- [ ] No new one-off button styled as an input unless added to `shared/` for reuse
